# Teaching: Signal — WAI Closeout Bug Fixes (4 issues) from Minder Session 51

**Type:** signal
**safe_to_auto_adopt:** true

---

## What This Teaching Does

Appends 4 bug-fix signals to the spoke's lug store, correcting recurring issues found in `wai-closeout.md`. All fixes are safe to apply immediately.

---

## Why It Matters

These bugs affected every closeout silently. The banner stall was recurring in sessions 47–48. The bytype/session-log issues caused steps to fail or skip without explanation.

---

## Embedded Signals

```json
{"id":"fix-closeout-banner-stall-v1","ty":"signal","s":"o","title":"Closeout Step 10: invert confirmation logic — proceed unless explicit cancel","signal":"Step 10 banner previously required explicit affirmative. Any side comment, question, or non-yes response caused indefinite stall. Fix: proceed by default. Only stop on explicit 'no', 'cancel', 'stop', 'abort', or 'wait'. Questions answered then commit continues without re-presenting banner. Banner text: 'Proceeding in 10s — reply cancel to stop.'","impact":9,"created_at":"2026-03-28T01:00:00Z","created_by":"claude-sonnet-4-6"}
{"id":"fix-closeout-bytype-assumption-v1","ty":"signal","s":"o","title":"Closeout Steps 5b/5c: add bytype/ capability check before running","signal":"Steps 5b and 5c assume bytype/ directory structure. Flat-lug spokes silently skip all per-type file operations, producing no output and no error. Fix: add capability check at start of 5b — if WAI-Spoke/lugs/bytype/ does not exist, log 'flat-lug spoke — Steps 5b/5c skipped' and jump to 5d.","impact":5,"created_at":"2026-03-28T01:00:00Z","created_by":"claude-sonnet-4-6"}
{"id":"fix-closeout-health-check-missing-v1","ty":"signal","s":"o","title":"Closeout Step 9d: health-check.jsonl template does not exist — skip is expected","signal":"Step 9d loads templates/health-check.jsonl. This file does not exist in the framework. Every spoke logs a spurious 'file not found' error every session. Fix: annotate Step 9d — template is intentionally absent until created. Skip is expected, not an error. Log 'Step 9d: health-check.jsonl not found, skipping.'","impact":6,"created_at":"2026-03-28T01:00:00Z","created_by":"claude-sonnet-4-6"}
{"id":"fix-session-log-retired-v1","ty":"signal","s":"o","title":"WAI-Session-Log.jsonl retired — no agent writes to it, use sessions/track_*.jsonl","signal":"WAI-Session-Log.jsonl appears in wai.md and wai-status.md as an active file but no agent has a write contract for it. It is always empty. Session tracking is handled by sessions/track_*.jsonl files. Fix: mark WAI-Session-Log.jsonl as retired in all references. Direct agents to sessions/ directory for session tracking.","impact":4,"created_at":"2026-03-28T01:00:00Z","created_by":"claude-sonnet-4-6"}
```

